{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "08", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "14", "M": "15", "S": "00"}}, "news": [{"title": "Centre launches \u20b933,500 crore Delhi infrastructure push, including housing and metro projects", "para": "Prime minister Narendra Modi launched development projects valued at approximately \u20b933,500 crore in Delhi. These initiatives encompass metro expansion, government housing redevelopment, and urban infrastructure enhancements. Newly constructed government flats and office spaces were inaugurated. Foundation stones were laid for more GPRA flats and commercial office towers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/massive-33500-crore-infrastructure-boost-in-delhi-modi-unveils-new-metro-housing-projects/129273373?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-144456/129273373.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "PM inaugurates two new Delhi metro corridors", "para": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated two new Delhi Metro corridors, the Majlis Park-Maujpur Babarpur (Pink Line) and Deepali Chowk-Majlis Park (Magenta Line), enhancing connectivity for several areas. He also laid the foundation stone for three new Phase V-A corridors, including routes to the airport and connecting Noida with south Delhi, as part of a Rs 33,500 crore infrastructure development.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/pm-modi-unveils-new-delhi-metro-corridors-boosting-connectivity/129273675?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-79718/129273675.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Over 4,100 transit flats for Kashmiri migrant employees completed in Valley", "para": "Construction of transit flats for Kashmiri migrant employees is progressing well. Over 4,100 of the 6,000 planned flats are now complete. The remaining units are anticipated to be finished by the end of next month. Essential services are being reviewed to ensure readiness for occupancy. Further flats are scheduled for completion by April 2026.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/over-4100-transit-flats-completed-for-kashmiri-migrant-employees-in-valley/129272865?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-72660/129272865.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}